news.title: Asian investor's share in Indian real estate surges to 47% in 2023: Report
news.para: Transaction volumes have increased by over 25% annually, with investment values rising 13.7%, reaching USD 3.9 billion in recent years.

news.title: How sustainable technologies transform home elements and building practices
news.para: Companies functioning in real estate segment are increasingly transforming their operations while integrating green measures.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 14 crore property tax in first two weeks of April
news.para: NMC officials said they have plans to garner around Rs 50 crore in April of the current financial year 2024-25, Apart from 8% rebate, the civic body has also introduced an additional 1% rebate if the taxpayers pay their bills online.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body to file cases against property tax defaulters
news.para: 800 property owners in Hyderabad face legal action for bouncing cheques to GHMC, impacting tax collection. GHMC accepts online transactions, demand drafts. Issue discovered during financial audit.

news.title: Citizens in Ahmedabad take dim view of irregular street lights
news.para: ​Dimly lit streets, uneven pole heights and no standard design or distance between street lights mean complaints have piled up with the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC).

news.title: Kolkata civic body considers ordinance route to punish errant builders
news.para: On Saturday, mayor Firhad Hakim met municipal commissioner and senior officials from the buildings and law departments to chalk out the modalities for placing the amendment proposal before the KMC House.

news.title: HCC to raise Rs 350 crore via rights issue
news.para: The rights issue committee approved the allotment of 166,666,666 equity shares at a price of Rs 21 each, the civil construction firm said in a filing to the BSE.

news.title: Canada to lease government land in plan to add millions of homes
news.para: The government said the land is underutilized. The property could potentially include abandoned industrial parks, sites of defunct government companies and schools with low enrollment.

news.title: Thailand's Central Group buys Germany's KaDeWe Group
news.para: Central said in a statement on Friday that it was optimistic about talks to acquire the entire KaDeWe Group, which includes Alsterhaus in Hamburg, and Oberpollinger in Munich.

news.title: Adani Group targets 20% share in Indian cement market by FY28
news.para: Besides, Adani Cement also amplifies the pace of capacity expansion and is expected to have an accelerated growth rate of 16 per cent to reach 140 MTPA (million tonnes per annum) by FY2028.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' sales up 26% in FY24
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers' annual sales volumes stood at 3.92 million sq ft in FY24 as against 3.27 million sq ft, registering a 20 per cent year-on-year growth.

news.title: Bengaluru: BAF signs MoU with BWSSB to sell treated water at Rs 8 per kilolitre
news.para: Satish Mallya, Vice President of BAF, said that money is not the primary agenda of supplying the STP water but it is about ensuring water does not get wasted.

news.title: Property tycoon's death sentence is a turning point in Vietnam's anti-corruption campaign
news.para: The real estate sector in particular is floundering. An estimated 1,300 property firms withdrew from the market in 2023 and high-rises lie empty in major cities like Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh.

news.title: Canada to allow some first-time home buyers to pay off mortgage in 30 years
news.para: The move, to be proposed in the upcoming federal budget, will help younger consumers afford a monthly mortgage payment and encourage new supply, Freeland told reporters in Toronto.

news.title: Sweden’s SBB postpones earnings report of Q1 2024
news.para: High debt, high interest rates and a wilting economy have hit many European property companies, with the sector in Sweden among the worst affected.

news.title: SEBI imposes penalties on Prabhu Steel Industries, three others
news.para: Sebi has slapped penalties totalling Rs 12 lakh on Prabhu Steel Industries Ltd (PSIL), its promoters including Harish Gangaram Agarwal, Dinesh Gangaram Agarwal and Akshita Harish Agarwal for flouting regulatory norms.
